 of work in the new cultural economy, Pricing Beauty offers rich, accessible analysis of the invisible ways in which gender, race, and class shape worth in the marketplace.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFashion shows. 0aModeling agencies. 0aModels (Persons) 0aModels (Persons). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  abeauty consumption.  abeauty standards.  acultural economy.  acultural production.  acultural theory.  aculture studies.  aethnography.  afashion economy.  afashion industry.  afashion models.  afashion studies.  afashion world.  afemale models.  agender studies.  ainsider perspective.  alondon.  amale models.  amodeling agents.  amodeling politics.  amodeling.  anew york.  anonfiction.  apersonal observations.  aphotographers.  arace and class.  arunway models.  aselling beauty.  asocial science.  asociologists.  asociology.  astylists.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026033740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095021440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520950214423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520950214/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY